TY  - JOUR
TI  - A Theory of Chosen Preferences
AU  - Bernheim, B. Douglas
AU  - Braghieri, Luca
AU  - Martínez-Marquina, Alejandro
AU  - Zuckerman, David
AB  - [We propose and develop a dynamic theory of endogenous preference formation in which people adopt worldviews that shape their judgments about their experiences. The framework highlights the role of mindset flexibility, a trait that determines the relative weights the decision-maker places on her current and anticipated worldviews when evaluating future outcomes. The theory generates rich behavioral dynamics, thereby illuminating a wide range of applications and providing potential explanations for a variety of observed phenomena.]
